From: scheme <scheme@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] mlx4: retain RoCEv2 capability for VF behind patched PF

The inbox mlx4 VF path clears MLX4_FLAG_ROCE_V1_V2 during capability
discovery because an unmodified PF does not support all of the VF RoCEv2
address programming path.  When the PF runs this repository's host patch,
it accepts and preserves MLX4_SET_PORT_ROCE_ADDR including the GID type.

Do not hide the reported RoCEv2 capability in the VF guest.  This allows
the stock mlx4_ib RoCEv2 implementation in the guest to expose RoCEv2 GIDs
and program RoCEv2 QPs through the patched PF.

This guest patch requires the host-side CX3 Pro inbox patch.
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/fw.c | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/fw.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/fw.c
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/fw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx4/fw.c
@@ -1398,7 +1398,10 @@ static void disable_unsupported_roce_caps(void *buf)
 	flags &= ~(1UL << 24);
 	MLX4_PUT(buf, flags, QUERY_DEV_CAP_EXT_2_FLAGS_OFFSET);
 	MLX4_GET(flags, buf, QUERY_DEV_CAP_BMME_FLAGS_OFFSET);
-	flags &= ~(MLX4_FLAG_ROCE_V1_V2);
+	/*
+	 * Keep RoCEv2 for VFs when the PF accepts MLX4_SET_PORT_ROCE_ADDR
+	 * and retains its GID type, as supplied by the host-side patch.
+	 */
 	MLX4_PUT(buf, flags, QUERY_DEV_CAP_BMME_FLAGS_OFFSET);
 }
 
